---
import { photo, images } from '../data';
---

<section class="maker" id="maker">
  <div class="wrap maker-grid">
    <figure class="maker-figure reveal">
      <div class="maker-frame">
        <img
          src={photo(images.maker, 1000)}
          srcset={`${photo(images.maker, 700)} 700w, ${photo(images.maker, 1100)} 1100w`}
          sizes="(max-width: 900px) 92vw, 42vw"
          width="700"
          height="840"
          loading="lazy"
          alt="The maker at the workbench, tools within reach, sawdust on the surface."
        />
      </div>
    </figure>

    <div class="maker-copy">
      <h2 class="reveal">Made by one person, on purpose.</h2>
      <div class="maker-text reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 90ms">
        <p>
          I run Craftasaurus on my own. I draw it, cut it, forge it, and finish
          it. No production line, no outsourcing, no piece leaving here that I
          would not keep myself.
        </p>
        <p>
          When something carries a plane mark or a hammer face, that is not a
          flaw to sand away. It is the proof that a person made it, for you, out
          of a real material that will age and last.
        </p>
      </div>
      <dl class="maker-facts reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 160ms">
        <div>
          <dt>Materials</dt>
          <dd>Solid hardwood, mild and tool steel, laser-cut wood.</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>Made to order</dt>
          <dd>Sized, finished, and signed for you.</dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .maker {
    padding-block: clamp(4rem, 9vw, 8rem);
    background: var(--surface-2);
  }
  .maker-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 0.9fr 1.1fr;
    gap: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4.5rem);
    align-items: center;
  }

  .maker-figure { margin: 0; }
  .maker-frame {
    position: relative;
    border-radius: var(--radius);
    overflow: hidden;
    box-shadow: 0 30px 60px -38px oklch(0.235 0.012 55 / 0.55);
  }
  .maker-frame::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 1px var(--hairline);
    border-radius: var(--radius);
  }
  .maker-frame img {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 5 / 6;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .maker-copy h2 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4.2vw, 3.2rem);
    margin: 0 0 1.3rem;
  }
  .maker-text p {
    margin: 0 0 1rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    max-width: 54ch;
  }
  .maker-text p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  .maker-facts {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 2.5rem;
    margin: 2rem 0 0;
    padding-top: 1.75rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--hairline);
  }
  .maker-facts dt {
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ember);
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
  }
  .maker-facts dd {
    margin: 0;
    font-weight: 500;
    max-width: 22ch;
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .maker-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 2.25rem; }
    .maker-figure { max-width: 28rem; }
  }
</style>
